Moments ago I was in a meeting where the owner of the company expressed great interest in entering and expanding in the social media/online presence realm. 
When diving into details he cited wanting a "worker" and considered entrepreneurial talent "bad for business". How those two can be deemed separate of one another is pretty damn hilarious and one of the reasons I urge those of you with budding talents to stop taking pennies at shit jobs under uninformed bosses. 
While it's understandable that many of you would love to have experts in house it's also becoming more and more apparent why so many companies FAIL at the social media/online game, or innovation at that.

In all honesty it's why cities like Miami typically remain behind on so many fronts, the game has been changing for some time now, and innovation and intellect wins eventually. I mean, it's kinda hard to ignore that @tesla is now worth more than General Motors ....
